Description: Pottery sherd from vessel: part of body and handle. Black burnished.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Curator's comments: No longer seen as Minoan influenced: possibly imitating Levantine pottery. Nile silt fabric. Fitton, J.L., Hughes, M. and Quirke, S. (1998), ‘Northerners at Lahun: Neutron Activation Analysis of Minoan and related pottery in the British Museum’, in S. Quirke (ed.) Lahun Studies, p. 124
